Do not take additional techs to 162 and 168; the former alone is a lot of work, saying this as someone who's done this combination before. I believe I also took math 110 that semester and I spent virtually no time on it (not even doing the vast majority of homework, which was optional; I consider myself a very strong math student).

Also rising junior doing 162/168; doing Physics 7B alongside it so I can focus on 162. If you're eecs then that would work!

children.subject: ^ One important, but often-neglected, consideration is that compatibility of schedules is just as important as competency in coding. If you're unable to meet to create and agree on design, good coding skills will be of little use.

Hi! I also happen to be a rising junior taking 162+168 this fall. Would either of you by any chance be interested in forming a project group for 162 (that is, if you don't have one already)? I also plan to put my main focus on that class, and I'm very good with completing projects thoroughly and on time.
